sec.p:
Overall, on the basis of the available scientific literature, it can be stated that the development of an effective joint must meet certain fundamental conditions:


the surface of the rivet head should appear parallel to the surface sheet (certain geometric conditions between rivet head and sheet must be guaranteed);

the die does not generate cracks on sheet.
There are also some disadvantages related to the use of this joining technique:


possibility of galvanic corrosion between metal plates of different materials and sheet metals and rivet;

weight gain due to the presence of the rivet itself.
